{"word":"ἀναπείθω","slug":"ἀναπείθω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀναπείθω</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to bring over, convince</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to persuade, move</i> to do a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic; <el>ἀν. τινά τι</el> <i>to persuade</i> one <i>of</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to seduce, mislead</i>, <el>τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}